This is mainly the area of what is called the continental shelf, which often extends several hundred kilometres from the coast of the given country.
The latter may, according to the Convention, claim exclusively to all the resources of the continental shelf.
"In order to simplify, the part of the seabed and its subsoil, which is a natural extension of the continent under the sea, is considered as a continental shelf.
