William Woodruff
Professor John Beckett writes:
Your obituary by William Woodruff (died 25 September) states that "in 1946 he had resumed his studies in economic history at Oxford and became a member of Houblon-Norma research in 1950 while he was doing a BSc, an MA and a PhD".
